description: Our heroes follow a fleet of submarines back to Black Ghost's lair where 009 finally meets his arch-enemy, Black Ghost, face to face. The ensuing battle causes the destruction of Black Ghost's island as 009 and his companions escape to Japan.
name: Vol. 2

description: 009's search for their kidnapped ally begins to test friendship and loyalty when 009 gets baited into a trap. But if he can find the elusive 0013, 009 may just be able to get closer to the ubiquitous Black Ghost. Then, as neo-Nazis threaten the world and an evil scientist kidnaps the children from Japan's most powerful families, the cyborg team must come together as one and fight for justice.
name: Vol. 3

description: A renegade Black Ghost scientist with a highly advanced android at his side warns of the evil organization's plans to launch a missile satellite into outer space--a weapon that will give them the power to destroy any city on Earth in a matter of seconds. And when tensions flare in Vietnam, the cyborgs suspect the Viet Cong of getting help from an outside party.
name: Vol. 4

description: Machines in the Jungle... As war rages in South Vietnam, the cyborgs are confronted by group of guerillas led by a mysterious masked man who has a diabolical plan. With the Black Ghost never far behind, the cyborgs uncover an evil scheme that just might lead to global Armageddon. But before they can act, they must save one of their own from behind enemy lines.
name: Vol. 5

description: After our double-zero heroes make their way through the jungles of Vietnam, they step out of the frying pan and into a greater fire. The mighty powerful Greek Myutos Cyborg team has heard about their victory in 'Nam and would like to initiate a little tete-a-tete offensive. Never one to shy away from a Sisyphean challenge, our cyborg super group steps up to battle...but will they sing paeans of victory? Or will the Herculean strength of the Greek team find 009's Achilles' heel?
name: Vol. 6

description: Our double-zero heroes clash with Atlas, the XXXL Greek Myutos cyborg. The vicious battle wreaks havoc on 009, whose vital signs approach 000. Meanwhile, Dr. Uranus butts heads with a giant dinosaur that wants to use the steel supermen as fossil fuel. It's an international adventure filled with fire-breathing lions, a chaotic canine, and a drive down the Champs-Elysees in gay old Paris!
name: Vol. 7

description: Four years have passed since our heroes' last adventure, and the mechanistic macho men seek to retire to the simple live. However, 009 remains as fast and furious as his nom de guerre, Hurricane Joe, a hotshot race car driver. But a yellow flag is raised when Joe encounters the mysterious, dark power of the Black Ghost. Just when 009 thinks he's out, they keep dragging him back in!
name: Vol. 8

description: 009 has double vision when he sees two Helens--although their faces aren't launching a thousand ships, they sink 009 into a ball of confusion. The rest of our alloy alliance is in for a double--crossing. While closing in on the Black Ghost, a member of gang zero--zero turns out to be a big fat zero!
name: Vol. 9

description: Ghost in the Machine In the unrelenting battle with the Black Ghost, our double-O heroes have traveled around the world, dived to the murky depths of the oceans and rocketed to the cool, far reaches of outer space. All the while, the Black Ghost has paved a path for perpetual war... but now all roads must come to an end. In this grand finale, the Teflon team journeys deep into the ranks of the Black Ghost, all the way to its secret, central command! But what 009 finds will shock the mechanical daylights out of him. Will the Black Ghost pull the plug on the ennead ensemble once and for all? Or will the machines finally destroy their creator?
name: Vol. 10

description: The story "Water, Water, Who's Got the Water?" is the first appearance of Snagglepuss in comics.
name: Water, Water, Who's Got the Water?

1 page story "Dinner date Data!" - Inside front cover. Black & white, 6-panel sequence presenting dinner date tips and advice.

1 page Table of Contents story "First Love Contents"

1 page filler "Young Ideas from the Love Scrapbook"

5 page story "A Love For a Life"

1 page story "Is It Love?" - 6 panel sequence providing compatibility advice.

1 page text story "Double in Hearts!"

5 page story "Grasp at a Straw"

4 page story "The Love That Wasn't Mine!"

6 page story "Choose Well, My Heart!"

1 page text story "Cupid Scores High!"

5 page story "Tragic Awakening"

1 page story "For Hunters Only!" - "To catch her man, a gal must know the rules! Like any other hunter, she's got to know how to trap her quarry and bring him in alive! The rules are simple..." 5 panel sequence. Tongue-in-cheek "hunter's guide" for women.

1 page story "Time of Trial"

1 page (back cover) "Wrong Kind of Guy" Inside back cover. 6 panel black & white sequence.

The Celebrated Cases of Dick Tracy 1931-1951

volume.name: The Celebrated Cases of Dick Tracy 1931-1951

description:
Daisuke Niwa is an ordinary middle school student who has inherited an interesting family condition. Upon seeing Risa, the girl he adores, he transforms into a daring phantom thief. When the phantom thief sees his own object of desire, he turns back into Daisuke. The only way to cure this craziness is if Daisuke can get Risa to fall in love with him, but how can she love someone she can't see?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Warning of Trouble and Romance
  • Chapter 2: Warning of A Level Up and Illusions
  • Chapter 3: Second Warning of A Fallen Angel
  • "N" Is For Nishiki
name: Volume 1

description: The annual midwinter hike is no walk in the park for the students of Azumano Middle School. Daisuke has been dreading the trek all year, but his one ray of hope is that he gets to show off his mountain expertise for his beloved Risa. But when Daisuke and Riku are forced off the beaten path, will their excursion turn into a real cliffhanger?
name: Vol. 2

description: It's time for the St. White festival, and Daisuke has been so busy working on the festival committee that he's forgotten to get a present for his beloved Risa. His mother, in her infinite generosity, forces Daisuke to take a simple white ribbon as a gift. To top it all off, there's a story going around that if a boy gives a white ribbon to a girl and ties it for her on St. White, they will fall in love...
name: Vol. 3

description: While continuing his relentless pursuit to get the scoop on Dark Mousy, Takeshi becomes distracted by a mysterious young woman in a museum. He falls instantly head over heels for her, and recruits Daisuke to help find out who she is. But the path to love takes them far from home...
name: Vol. 4

description: After barely escaping the fight with Krad, Daisuke find himself with no one to turn to. He has a new enemy out to kill him and Dark is nowhere to be found. When Daisuke receives a clue about Dark's whereabouts, he goes on a search-and-rescue mission for the phantom thief. Meanwhile, Riku and Risa manage to get each other lost, sending their classmates into a manic panic!
name: Vol. 5

description: Daisuke has the hots for Riku but doesn't have the guts to tell her. His whole family follows him into the forests where they watch Daisuke and Riku on their little date. Everyone is tired of waiting for this young man to make his move. Will he finally tell her?
name: Vol. 6

description: Things go from bad to worse when Daisuke is taken away by Time's Second-Hand, which Dark failed to steal. The only remaining link to Daisuke lies within the painting, which he had unwittingly given to Riku the day before. Dark now has to retrieve the painting--while pretending to be Daisuke!
name: Vol. 7

description: Sick of living in the sewers and in the shadows, Raphael decides to reveal his ninja turtle nature to a little girl.  But everything spins out of control when her mother sees him.  The raging reptile's appearance throws everyone's life into disarray and Raphael needs to fix his mistake before anything, or anyone, gets permanently damaged.
name: Shadow of the Mind's Eye

description: The Artist and the Thief Dark has retrieved the painting from Riku...but the sisters decide to get it back. What they don't know is that Daisuke is actually trapped in the painting and Dark has to set him free before time runs out! Humanity is questioned and love put to the test in this exciting volume of DNAngel!
name: Vol. 8

description: The production of the class play finally hits the stage, and even though Daisuke was a little embarrassed to play a girl, he soon realizes that giving a good performance in the part of Freedert is the least he can do for his magical friend. Later, there's a series of transformations and troubled sleep, when a near kiss from Daisuke to Riku changes him into Dark. Then, when Dark plants one on Risa, he changes back into Daisuke--something that has never happened before!
name: Vol. 9

description: When Risa and Dark--who's actually Wiz in disguise--go to a popular new horror movie, Wiz is nearly scared to death! Meanwhile, Riku and Daisuke are enjoying their time alone, although Daisuke's trying not to have too good of a time, lest he change into Dark and blow the whole thing. Later, Risa expresses her unconditional love for Dark, who hints that he may not be everything he seems.
name: Vol. 10

description: In this much-anticipated volume of D.N.Angel, Daisuke and Dark are placed in-between a rock and a hard place after an unknown enemy kidnaps Risa thinking she is the "Sacred Maiden." Daisuke is torn by his feelings of anger, and pain drives Dark further away from helping him rescue Risa. Will Daisuke turn to Satoshi for help? Is Satoshi involved in the kidnapping? It's all inside the volume you've all been waiting for!
name: Vol. 11

description: In order to rescue Risa, his kidnapped classmate, Daisuke decides to team up with his longtime rival, Satoshi Hiwatari. Will they be up to the challenge against Argentine's dark plot?!
name: Vol. 12

description: The time has come for Satoshi to reveal to Daisuke the history behind the Hikari/Niwa curse... Just what is the tragic story behind the works of art left behind, and the family of thieves tasked with stealing them? And when Risa's life is threatened yet again, who will be the one to save her?
name: Vol. 13

description:
The gateway to hell is opened in this tale of demon bloodlust and angelic redemption.

Alone and disfigured from a tragic car accident in his childhood, Seisu is plagued by haunting visions and hellish nightmares. But when a stay at a remote monastery brings the mysterious young man Yabrail into his life, Seisu discovers not only what’s behind his fragile state of mind, and also that heaven and hell aren't as distant as he once believed...
name: Vol. 1

description: Dheeraj, Apirl O'Nei's first employee at the antique store, wants to become a better martial artist, but his brain keeps getting in the way of his fists.  He thinks too much, and when it comes down to the wire he chokes.  Luckily for him Leonardo sees some potential in him and decides to give him some lessons in the way of the ninja!
name: Bend it Like Turtles

description:
In the near future, the population lives in underwater. Ai Mayuzumi is the daughter of the head of the research lab in one of the underwater cites. When a terrorists attacks Ai's city, she becomes involved with an all-female counter-terrorist group! 

Chapter Titles 

  • Chapter 1 ... HELLO!
  • Chapter 2 ... The Impatient Girl's Blood Boils
  • Chapter 3 ... The Closed City
  • Chapter 4 ... The City of Light
  • Chapter 5 ... Ai, Here and Now
  • Chapter 6 ... Ai's Choice
name: Vol. 1

description: The Thoogs are ticked. Dheeraj made them look like fools with his kung fu skills and they're looking for some payback. But the turtles don't appreciate anyone messing with their friends, and so they decide to take matters into their own three-fingered hands.
name: Kali Flower

description: The ageless war between Light and Dark has finally burst forth from the shadows! Triple H has returned from the dead to take the fight to his brother – the Shadow King – and all hell will follow! Blood will flow and not everyone will walk away from this bout. See who wins and who loses in the ultimate WWE clash of the titans!
name: Rise of the Firstborn part 6

description: The official comics adaptation of the blockbuster film STAR TREK comes to an epic conclusion in this mini-series presented by J.J. Abrams , Roberto Orci  and Alex Kurtzman ! Kirk, Spock and the crew of the Enterprise fight to save Earth from Vulcan's fate! Brought to you by the creative team behind the best-selling STAR TREK: COUNTDOWN , this series includes scenes not included in the original film!

Dark Horse is proud to present the second manga series in its Neon Genesis Evangelion line, Neon Genesis Evangelion: Campus Apocalypse!

Shinji Ikari's parents are gone, and he lives with his legal guardian, Ryoji Kaji, while attending the private NERV Academy. But no one ever told Shinji about its secrets... or that he'd find his fellow students Kaworu, Rei, and Asuka out on the streets late at night -- fighting with sword, spear, and whip against an enemy that looks very human, but who Kaworu insists are beings called the Angels...

An original alternate-reality view of the characters and conflicts from the original Evangelion story, this debut from manga creator Mingming spins a dark web of romance, battle, and mystery.

Chapter Titles

  • First Event
  • Second Event
  • Third Event
  • Fourth Event
name: Vol. 1

description: There's a new hunk in town and Veronica has her sights set on him. She latches on to Kevin, but despite her increasingly persistent attempts to get his attention, he's just not interested! Jughead takes advantage of the situation and uses them both in his quest to play Veronica for a fool. In the end, will Jughead turn out to be the real dunce?
name: Isn't It Bro-mantic?

description: Two Torchwood comic adventures! In 'Fated to Pretend', the Torchwood team get stuck in a prison ... surrounded by deadly zombies! Plus, Jack, Gwen and Ianto face the threat of Bilis Manger in Part Two of 'Broken'!
name: Fated to Pretend; Broken part 2 of 5; The Man Who Dreamed of Stars
